<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB6FFECFF1CFA6E4D17FE3E" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFF1CFA6E4831F93E" blockId="7.[113,764,1463,1935]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFF1CFA6E4985FA3E" box="[151,231,1464,1487]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFE39FA614BE5FA3E" author="BURMAN" box="[434,647,1463,1487]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="231" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 231)</bibRefCitation>
referred to two plates (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFF61FA0148C0FA1E" author="RHEEDE" box="[234,418,1495,1519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref10115" refString="RHEEDE [TOT DRAAKESTEIN], H. A. VAN (1678 - 1693). Hortus Indicus Malabaricus. 12 vol. Amsterdam. [vol. 12, 1693]" type="book" year="1693">RHEEDE, 1693: 41</bibRefCitation>
, tab. 20, 21) and did not mention any collector, but “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFEB8FA214B3BF9FE" box="[307,601,1527,1551]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Habitat in 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFE2FFA2E48B1F9FE" box="[420,467,1528,1551]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
&amp; Malabara
</emphasis>
” as locality and the Javanese vernacular names “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFE35F9C14B73F9DE" box="[446,529,1559,1583]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Kakajar</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFDDEF9C14BA2F9DE" box="[597,704,1559,1583]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Tally kaffa</emphasis>
”. The latter should be regarded as specimen citation, since these names are not mentioned in the cited publication. The existence of a Javan gathering is confirmed by Burman’s concluding remark (“ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFF5CF94E4BDDF95E" box="[215,703,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">In Javanica foliorum foramina non observantur</emphasis>
”. See 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFFFAF9614825F93E" author="MERRILL" box="[113,327,1719,1743]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="342" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL, 1921: 342</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFF1CF90148AFF8BE" blockId="7.[113,764,1463,1935]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Asingle gathering in G-PREL [G00348760], consisting of a giant leaf, matches this specimen citation; it bears both Javanese names “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFEA6F8C148E1F8DE" box="[301,387,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Kakajar</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFE40F8C14B5FF8DE" box="[459,573,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Tally kassa</emphasis>
”, and the species name from N.L. Burman’s hand.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFF1CF8814D4DFE9E" blockId="7.[113,764,1463,1935]" lastBlockId="7.[801,1451,279,463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Nicolson in 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFE91F88148BCF89E" author="SMITH" box="[282,478,1879,1903]" firstAuthor="SMITH" journalOrPublisher="Allertonia" page="346" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="331 - 414" part="1" refId="ref10292" refString="SMITH, A. C. (1978). A precursor to a new Flora of Fiji. Allertonia 1: 331 - 414." title="A precursor to a new Flora of Fiji" type="journal article" year="1978">SMITH (1978: 346)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to discuss the typification of Burman’s name: “In Burman’s herbarium (G), there is a leaf specimen, […] to be regarded as the 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB6FFECFAD5FEC14CEFFEDE" box="[1374,1421,279,303]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFCAAFEE14D03FEBF" authority="Burm." authorityName="Burm." box="[801,1121,311,335]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laciniatum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFCAAFEE14D76FEBE" box="[801,1044,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Polypodium laciniatum</emphasis>
Burm.
</taxonomicName>
f.”. This is regarded as a valid implicit lectotypification.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFCCCFEA14D17FE3E" blockId="7.[801,1451,279,463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
The type specimen represents a leaf of 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFA97FEAE4A98FE5F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFA97FEAE4AEBFE5E" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Epipremnum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinnatum">Epipremnum pinnatum</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB6FFECFC13FE414A8DFE5F" box="[920,1007,407,430]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Araceae</taxonomicName>
),
</emphasis>
“a common and weedy species of 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFAF3FE414CC0FE5E" box="[1400,1442,407,431]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
” (Nicolson in 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFC26FE614D0BFE3E" author="SMITH" box="[941,1129,439,463]" firstAuthor="SMITH" journalOrPublisher="Allertonia" page="346" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="331 - 414" part="1" refId="ref10292" refString="SMITH, A. C. (1978). A precursor to a new Flora of Fiji. Allertonia 1: 331 - 414." title="A precursor to a new Flora of Fiji" type="journal article" year="1978">SMITH, 1978: 346</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
